FT  15 JAN 94 / Markets: House prices rise in final quarter of '93 - At a
glance
House prices across the UK were an average of 2.9 per cent higher in the
final quarter of 1993 than in the same period of 1992, according to the
Nationwide building society. Prices were higher in nine regions out of 13.
The highest increase was 11 per cent in Scotland, while the north-west
recorded a fall of 4.4 per cent.
Fourth quarter prices were marginally lower than in the third quarter of
1993, down 0.1 per cent on average, although London buyers paid 5.1 per cent
more than in the previous three months.
The average price paid by first time buyers in the fourth quarter was Pounds
39,909, while previous owner-occupiers paid Pounds 65,697 on average.
